parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Excessive Oil Consumption and Engine Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive oil consumption can lead to engine failure, causing the vehicle to stall or leave the driver stranded, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle burns excessive amounts of oil (1 quart or more every 500 to 1000 miles)
the engine makes a ticking or grinding noise
the oil light on the dashboard blinks or stays on
and the engine may eventually fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The weak valves can cause engine failure, leading to the vehicle stalling or leaving the driver stranded, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine makes a clicking or grinding noise
the vehicle burns excessive amounts of oil
and the engine may eventually fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the belt tensioner can cause the engine to fail, leading to the vehicle stalling or leaving the driver stranded, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The belt tensioner squeals and makes noise
especially when humid.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive oil consumption in the 1ZZ-FE engine can cause engine failure, leading to loss of power, stalling, and potentially fatal accidents. It can also lead to environmental pollution due to the excessive oil burning.
symptoms: The engine consumes excessive amounts of oil
often requiring frequent oil additions
loud ticking or knocking sounds
engine light stays on or flashes
loss of power
and engine stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause loss of gear shifting, grinding noises, and even complete loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or stranding.
symptoms: Grinding noise while shifting
inability to shift gears
loud noise while driving
loss of engine power
RPMs dropping
throwing the car out of gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to premature engine wear, increased emissions, and potentially cause engine failure, resulting in costly repairs or even accidents.
symptoms: Consuming 1.5 quarts of oil every 500 miles
excessive oil consumption starting at 96
000 miles.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch malfunction can cause difficulty shifting gears, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, or stranding.
symptoms: Repeated clutch malfunction
clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position.
